CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS orders (order_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, product_id INT REFERENCES products(id), quantity INT, order_date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS suppliers (supplier_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), address VARCHAR(255), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><stat>SELECT s.name AS supplier_name, COUNT(*) AS total_orders FROM suppliers s JOIN products p ON s.supplier_id = p.id JOIN orders o ON p.id = o.product_id GROUP BY s.name</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS products (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS orders (order_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, product_id INT REFERENCES products(id), quantity INT, order_date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS suppliers (supplier_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), address VARCHAR(255), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><stat>select s.name as supplier_name, count(*) as total_orders from suppliers s join products p on s.supplier_id = p.id join orders o on p.id = o.product_id group by s.name</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS products (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS suppliers (supplier_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), address VARCHAR(255), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><stat>SELECT s.name AS supplier_name, AVG(p.price) AS avg_price FROM suppliers s JOIN products p ON s.supplier_id = p.id GROUP BY s.name HAVING AVG(p.price) > 50</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS products (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS suppliers (supplier_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), address VARCHAR(255), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><stat>SELECT p.name, COUNT(*) AS total_orders FROM products p JOIN orders o ON p.id = o.product_id GROUP BY p.name HAVING COUNT(*) > 10</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS products (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE products (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10, 2), stock_quantity INT);</t><stat>select p.name as product_name, s.location as supplier_location, o.quantity as order_quantity from products p join suppliers s on p.id = s.id join orders o on p.id = o.product_id and s.id = o.supplier_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE products (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), price DECIMAL(10, 2), stock_quantity INT);

CREATE TABLE suppliers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), location VARCHAR(255));</t><stat>select p.name as product_name, s.location as supplier_location, o.quantity as order_quantity, s.name as supplier_name from products p join suppliers s on p.id = s.id join orders o on p.id = o.product_id and s.id = o.supplier_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE shipments (shipment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, supplier_id INT, shipment_date TIMESTAMP);

CREATE TABLE suppliers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), location VARCHAR(255));</t><stat>SELECT p.name AS product_name, s.location AS supplier_location, o.quantity AS order_quantity, s.name AS supplier_name, sh.shipment_date AS shipment_date FROM products p JOIN suppliers s ON p.id = s.id JOIN orders o ON p.id = o.product_id AND s.id = o.supplier_id JOIN shipments sh ON o.order_id = sh.order_id AND o.supplier_id = sh.supplier_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_id INT, supplier_id INT, quantity INT, order_date TIMESTAMP);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS Shipments (shipment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, customer_id INT, shipment_date DATE, delivery_status STRING);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS Products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name STRING, quantity INT, price DECIMAL);</t><stat>SELECT supplier_name, product_name, shipment_date FROM Suppliers INNER JOIN Products ON Suppliers.supplier_id = Products.product_id INNER JOIN Orders ON Products.product_id = Orders.product_id INNER JOIN Shipments ON Orders.order_id = Shipments.order_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS Orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_id INT, supplier_id INT, quantity INT, order_date DATE);
